[308] (w=84) " by \u001b]8;;https://github.com/markusylisiurunen\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4m@markusylisiurunen\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\)                                                             "
[309] (w=84) "                                                                                    "
[310] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;240;198;116m\u001b[1m[0.69.0] - 2026-04-22\u001b[22m\u001b[39m                                                              "
[311] (w=84) "                                                                                    "
[312] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;240;198;116m\u001b[1m### \u001b[22m\u001b[39m\u001b[38;2;240;198;116m\u001b[1mNew Features\u001b[22m\u001b[39m                                                                   "
[313] (w=84) "                                                                                    "
[314] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mTypeBox 1.x migration for extensions and SDK integrations, including             "
[315] (w=84) " TypeBox-native tool argument validation that now works in eval-restricted runtimes "
[316] (w=84) " such as Cloudflare Workers. See \u001b]8;;docs/extensions.md\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4mdocs/extensions.md\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\ and \u001b]8;;docs/sdk.md\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4mdocs/sdk.md\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\.                "
[317] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mStacked extension autocomplete providers via                                     "
[318] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mctx.ui.addAutocompleteProvider(...)\u001b[39m, allowing extensions to layer custom           "
[319] (w=84) " completion logic on top of built-in slash and path completion. See                 "
[320] (w=84) " \u001b]8;;docs/extensions.md#autocomplete-providers\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4mdocs/extensions.md#autocomplete-providers\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\ and                                      "
[321] (w=84) " \u001b]8;;examples/extensions/github-issue-autocomplete.ts\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4mexamples/extensions/github-issue-autocomplete.ts\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\.                                  "
[322] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mTerminating tool results via \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mterminate: true\u001b[39m, allowing custom tools to end on a  "
[323] (w=84) " final tool call without paying for an automatic follow-up LLM turn. See            "
[324] (w=84) " \u001b]8;;docs/extensions.md\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4mdocs/extensions.md\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\ and \u001b]8;;examples/extensions/structured-output.ts\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4mexamples/extensions/structured-output.ts\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\.                   "
[325] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mOSC 9;4 terminal progress indicators during agent streaming and compaction for   "
[326] (w=84) " supporting terminals.                                                              "
[327] (w=84) "                                                                                    "
[328] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;240;198;116m\u001b[1m### \u001b[22m\u001b[39m\u001b[38;2;240;198;116m\u001b[1mBreaking Changes\u001b[22m\u001b[39m                                                               "
[329] (w=84) "                                                                                    "
[330] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mMigrated first-party coding-agent code, SDK/examples/docs, and package metadata  "
[331] (w=84) " from \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m@sinclair/typebox\u001b[39m 0.34.x to \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mtypebox\u001b[39m 1.x. New extensions, SDK integrations,    "
[332] (w=84) " and pi packages should depend on and import from \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mtypebox\u001b[39m. Legacy extension loading "
[333] (w=84) " still aliases the root \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m@sinclair/typebox\u001b[39m package, but \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m@sinclair/typebox/compiler\u001b[39m   "
[334] (w=84) " is no longer shimmed. This migration also picks up the new \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m@mariozechner/pi-ai\u001b[39m     "
[335] (w=84) " TypeBox-native validator path, so tool argument validation now works in            "
[336] (w=84) " eval-restricted runtimes such as Cloudflare Workers instead of being skipped       "
[337] (w=84) " (\u001b]8;;https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/3112\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4m#3112\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\)                                                                            "
[338] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mSession-replacement commands now invalidate captured pre-replacement             "
[339] (w=84) " session-bound extension objects after \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mctx.newSession()\u001b[39m, \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mctx.fork()\u001b[39m, and            "
[340] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mctx.switchSession()\u001b[39m. Old \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mpi\u001b[39m and command \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mctx\u001b[39m references now throw instead of        "
[341] (w=84) " silently targeting the replaced session. Migration: if code needs to keep working  "
[342] (w=84) " in the replacement session after one of those calls, pass \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mwithSession\u001b[39m to that same "
[343] (w=84) " method and do the post-switch work there. In practice, move post-switch            "
[344] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mpi.sendUserMessage()\u001b[39m, \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mpi.sendMessage()\u001b[39m, and command-ctx/session-manager access     "
[345] (w=84) " into \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mwithSession\u001b[39m, and use only the \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mReplacedSessionContext\u001b[39m passed to that callback  "
[346] (w=84) " for session-bound operations. Footguns: \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mwithSession\u001b[39m runs after the old extension   "
[347] (w=84) " instance has already received \u001b[38;2;138;190;183msession_shutdown\u001b[39m, old cleanup may already have       "
[348] (w=84) " invalidated captured state, captured old \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mpi\u001b[39m / old command \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mctx\u001b[39m are stale, and       "
[349] (w=84) " previously extracted raw objects such as \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mconst sm = ctx.sessionManager\u001b[39m remain the  "
[350] (w=84) " caller's responsibility and must not be reused after the switch.                   "
[351] (w=84) "                                                                                    "
[352] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;240;198;116m\u001b[1m### \u001b[22m\u001b[39m\u001b[38;2;240;198;116m\u001b[1mAdded\u001b[22m\u001b[39m                                                                          "
[353] (w=84) "                                                                                    "
[354] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mAdded support for terminating tool results via \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mterminate: true\u001b[39m, allowing custom  "
[355] (w=84) " tools to end the current tool batch without an automatic follow-up LLM call, plus  "
[356] (w=84) " a \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mstructured-output.ts\u001b[39m extension example and extension docs showing the pattern    "
[357] (w=84) " (\u001b]8;;https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/3525\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4m#3525\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\)                                                                            "
[358] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mAdded OSC 9;4 terminal progress indicators during agent streaming and            "
[359] (w=84) " compaction, so terminals like iTerm2, WezTerm, Windows Terminal, and Kitty show    "
[360] (w=84) " activity in their tab bar                                                          "
[361] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mAdded \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mctx.ui.addAutocompleteProvider(...)\u001b[39m for stacking extension autocomplete    "
[362] (w=84) " providers on top of the built-in slash/path provider, plus a                       "
[363] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mgithub-issue-autocomplete.ts\u001b[39m example and extension docs (\u001b]8;;https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/2983\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4m#2983\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\)                    "
[364] (w=84) "                                                                                    "
[365] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;240;198;116m\u001b[1m### \u001b[22m\u001b[39m\u001b[38;2;240;198;116m\u001b[1mFixed\u001b[22m\u001b[39m                                                                          "
[366] (w=84) "                                                                                    "
[367] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mFixed exported session HTML to sanitize markdown link URLs before rendering them "
[368] (w=84) " into anchor tags, blocking \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mjavascript:\u001b[39m-style payloads while preserving safe links  "
[369] (w=84) " in shared/exported sessions (\u001b]8;;https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/3532\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4m#3532\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\)                                                "
[370] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mFixed \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mctx.getSystemPrompt()\u001b[39m inside \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mbefore_agent_start\u001b[39m to reflect chained         "
[371] (w=84) " system-prompt changes made by earlier \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mbefore_agent_start\u001b[39m handlers, and clarified   "
[372] (w=84) " the extension docs around provider-payload rewrites and what \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mctx.getSystemPrompt() "
[373] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m\u001b[39m does and does not report (\u001b]8;;https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/3539\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4m#3539\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\)                                                  "
[374] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mFixed built-in \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mgoogle-gemini-cli\u001b[39m model lists and selector entries to include     "
[375] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mgemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview\u001b[39m, so Cloud Code Assist users no longer need manual    "
[376] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m--model\u001b[39m fallback selection to use it (\u001b]8;;https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/3545\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4m#3545\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\)                                       "
[377] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mFixed extension session-replacement flows so \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mctx.newSession()\u001b[39m, \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mctx.fork()\u001b[39m,       "
[378] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mctx.switchSession()\u001b[39m, and imported-session replacements fully rebind before         "
[379] (w=84) " post-switch work runs, added \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mwithSession\u001b[39m replacement callbacks with fresh          "
[380] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mReplacedSessionContext\u001b[39m helpers, and make stale pre-replacement \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mpi\u001b[39m / \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mctx\u001b[39m            "
[381] (w=84) " session-bound accesses throw instead of silently targeting the wrong session       "
[382] (w=84) " (\u001b]8;;https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/2860\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4m#2860\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\)                                                                            "
[383] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mFixed \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mmodels.json\u001b[39m built-in provider overrides to accept \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mheaders\u001b[39m without          "
[384] (w=84) " requiring \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mbaseUrl\u001b[39m, so request-header-only overrides now load and apply correctly   "
[385] (w=84) " (\u001b]8;;https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/3538\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4m#3538\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\)                                                                            "
