[452] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mChanged SDK and CLI tool selection from cwd-bound built-in tool instances to     "
[453] (w=84) " tool-name allowlists. \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mcreateAgentSession({ tools })\u001b[39m now expects \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mstring[]\u001b[39m names     "
[454] (w=84) " such as \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m\"read\"\u001b[39m and \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m\"bash\"\u001b[39m instead of \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mTool[]\u001b[39m, \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m--tools\u001b[39m now allowlists built-in,      "
[455] (w=84) " extension, and custom tools by name, and \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m--no-tools\u001b[39m now disables all tools by      "
[456] (w=84) " default rather than only built-ins. Migrate SDK code from \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mtools: [readTool,        "
[457] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mbashTool]\u001b[39m to \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mtools: [\"read\", \"bash\"]\u001b[39m (\u001b]8;;https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/2835\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4m#2835\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\, \u001b]8;;https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/3452\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4m#3452\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\)                                "
[458] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mRemoved prebuilt cwd-bound tool and tool-definition exports from                 "
[459] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent\u001b[39m, including \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mreadTool\u001b[39m, \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mbashTool\u001b[39m, \u001b[38;2;138;190;183meditTool\u001b[39m, \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mwriteTool\u001b[39m,  "
[460] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mgrepTool\u001b[39m, \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mfindTool\u001b[39m, \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mlsTool\u001b[39m, \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mreadOnlyTools\u001b[39m, \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mcodingTools\u001b[39m, and the corresponding      "
[461] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m*ToolDefinition\u001b[39m values. Use the explicit factory exports instead, for example      "
[462] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mcreateReadTool(cwd)\u001b[39m, \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mcreateBashTool(cwd)\u001b[39m, \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mcreateCodingTools(cwd)\u001b[39m, and              "
[463] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mcreateReadToolDefinition(cwd)\u001b[39m (\u001b]8;;https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/3452\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4m#3452\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\)                                              "
[464] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m- \u001b[39mRemoved ambient \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mprocess.cwd()\u001b[39m / default agent-dir fallback behavior from public  "
[465] (w=84) " resource helpers. \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mDefaultResourceLoader\u001b[39m, \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mloadProjectContextFiles()\u001b[39m, and            "
[466] (w=84) " \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mloadSkills()\u001b[39m now require explicit cwd/agent-dir style inputs, and exported         "
[467] (w=84) " system-prompt option types now require an explicit \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mcwd\u001b[39m. Pass the session or        "
[468] (w=84) " project cwd explicitly instead of relying on process-global defaults (\u001b]8;;https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/3452\u001b\\\u001b[38;2;129;162;190m\u001b[4m#3452\u001b[24m\u001b[39m\u001b]8;;\u001b\\)       "
