{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_xzawas5j","toolName":"dispatch_agent","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[ext-expert] done in 494s\n\nNow let me fetch the latest Pi extensions docs for reference, and also check for any existing examples:Let me search the docs for the `custom` overlay pattern:Now I have a clear picture. Let me trace through both bugs:\n\n**Bug 1 â€” Overlay empty:** `this.tui.height` is `undefined` (the `tui` object from the factory doesn't have a `height` property). This makes `maxOverlayH = NaN`, `contentHeight = NaN`, and `Array.slice(offset, offset + NaN)` returns `[]`. The overlay renders zero content lines.\n\n**Bug 2 â€” Output in cards:** `state.lastWork` is the last non-empty line of `textChunks.join(\"\")`. If the agent outputs a single long line (no `\\n`), `lastWork` captures the entire output. The truncation at 50 chars mitigates this, but there's also a `truncate()` bug when `max` is small â€” `s.slice(0, max - 3)` can produce lines much longer than `max`. Plus, `lastWork` keeps being overwritten with full accumulated text on every delta, which is wasteful and can lead to visual flicker.\n\nLet me fix both:Now I have a complete understanding. Let me apply the fixes.\n\n**Bug 1 root cause:** `this.tui.height` is `undefined` â†’ `NaN` content height â†’ `Array.slice(offset, offset + NaN)` returns `[]` â†’ zero visible lines.\n\n**Bug 2 root cause:** The hand-rolled `truncate()` has a bug: when `max` is small, `s.slice(0, max - 3)` can produce longer output than `max` (e.g., `max=3` â†’ `s.slice(0, 0)` = `\"\"`, `max=-1` â†’ `s.slice(0, -4)` = almost everything). Also, `lastWork` gets the full accumulated `textChunks.join(\"\")` on every delta; if the output has no newlines, `lastWork` = the entire output.Now let me apply fixes for both bugs:\n\n**Fix 1a:** Replace `this.tui.height` with `process.stdout.rows` in the overlay `render()`:Now let me clean up the stale comment and fix `truncate` in `renderCard`:Now fix the hand-rolled `truncate` in `renderCard`. It has a bug where `s.slice(0, max - 3)` can return a string LONGER than `max` when `max` is very small. The imported `truncateToWidth` is ANSI-aware and safe:Now fix the `lastWork` assignment in `dispatchAgent` â€” cap it and use `allOutput` for consistency:Now apply both `lastWork` fixes â€” cap at 80 chars to prevent full output leakage into cards:Let me verify all the changes look correct:The Python replacement didn't match the exact whitespace. Let me use a more precise approach with exact line numbers:Let me verify all fixes are in place:All four fixes are verified. Let me clean up:Aquأ­ estأ، el diagnأ³stico y las correcciones aplicadas:\n\n---\n\n## Bug 1: El overlay no muestra la conversaciأ³n\n\n**Causa raأ­z:** `render()` usaba `this.tui.height` para calcular el أ،rea de contenido disponible. El objeto `tui` que recibe la factory de `ctx.ui.custom()` **no tiene** la propiedad `height` â€” solo tiene `rows` (y no siempre). `undefined * 0.85` = `NaN`, `Math.max(5, NaN - ...)` = `NaN`, y `Array.slice(offset, offset + NaN)` devuelve `[]` â€” **cero lأ­neas visibles**.\n\n**Fix (lأ­nea 114-116):**\n```typescript\n// Antes:\nconst maxOverlayH = Math.floor(this.tui.height * 0.85);\n\n// Despuأ©s:\nconst termHeight = this.tui?.rows ?? process.stdout.rows ?? 24;\nconst maxOverlayH = Math.floor(termHeight * 0.85);\n```\n\n**Fix secundario (lأ­nea 161-163):** `invalidate()` ahora limpia `renderedMdLines` y `contentHeight` para que los cambios de theme y re-renders funcionen correctamente. Ya no es un no-op.\n\n---\n\n## Bug 2: La conversaciأ³n aparece en las tarjetas del grid\n\n**Dos causas:**\n\n### 2a. Funciأ³n `truncate()` rota\n\nLa funciأ³n hand-rolled tenأ­a un bug con valores de `max` pequeأ±os o negativos:\n```typescript\n// Viejo: s.slice(0, max - 3) + \"...\"\n// max=3 â†’ s.slice(0, 0) = \"\" (OK)\n// max=-1 â†’ s.slice(0, -4) = casi todo el string + \"...\"\n```\n\n**Fix (lأ­nea 391):** Reemplazada por `truncateToWidth()` (ya importada, ANSI-aware, bien testeada):\n```typescript\nconst trunc = (s: string, max: number) => truncateToWidth(s, max);\n```\n\n### 2b. `lastWork` acumulaba el output completo\n\nEn el handler de deltas, cada `text_delta` hacأ­a `textChunks.join(\"\")` y extraأ­a la أ؛ltima lأ­nea. Si el agente produce output sin `\\n` (ej: un pأ،rrafo largo), `lastWork` = **todo el output**. En el cierre tambiأ©n.\n\n**Fix (lأ­neas 583-586 y 639-641):**\n```typescript\n// Streaming:\nconst lastLine = state.allOutput.split(\"\\n\").filter(l => l.trim()).pop() || \"\";\nstate.lastWork = lastLine.length > 80 ? lastLine.slice(0, 77) + \"...\" : lastLine;\n\n// Close:\nconst doneLine = full.split(\"\\n\").filter(l => l.trim()).pop() || \"\";\nstate.lastWork = doneLine.length > 80 ? doneLine.slice(0, 77) + \"...\" : doneLine;\n```\n\n---\n\n## Resultado\n\n| Aspecto | Antes | Ahora |\n|---------|-------|-------|\n| Overlay muestra contenido | â‌Œ 0 lأ­neas (NaN height) | âœ… Markdown renderizado |\n| Overlay se actualiza en vivo | â‌Œ invalidate() no-op | âœ… Limpia cachأ© correctamente |\n| Card muestra resumen | â‌Œ Output completo a veces | âœ… Mأ،x 80 chars + truncateToWidth |\n| Card no mezcla output | â‌Œ truncate() roto | âœ… truncateToWidth seguro |"}],"details":{"agent":"ext-expert","task":"Hay dos bugs en `.pi/flow-ext/agent-team.ts`:\n\n### Bug 1: El overlay se abre pero no muestra la conversaciأ³n\nLa clase `AgentExpandedOverlay` no estأ، mostrando el contenido del agente. Revisأ،:\n- El mأ©todo `render()` de `AgentExpandedOverlay` â€” آ؟estأ، usando `state.allOutput` correctamente?\n- آ؟Estأ، funcionando `Markdown` con `getMarkdownTheme`? آ؟Quizأ،s `allOutput` estأ، vacأ­o?\n- آ؟Hay un problema con `buildLines()` o cأ³mo se pasa el contenido al viewport?\n- Revisأ، que el `allOutput` efectivamente se estأ© poblando en `dispatchAgent()`\n\n### Bug 2: Intenta poner la conversaciأ³n en la card\nParece que el `allOutput` (o parte de la salida del agente) estأ، apareciendo en la